Laser Corp said that costs associatedwith its defense of two shareholder lawsuits could result in anet loss for 1987.    Although Laser expects to post earnings from operations forthe year, a spokesman said they might be wiped out by legalcosts, depending on the length of litigation.    In addition, the company said it will ask shareholders toapprove proposals to merge the company into its mainsubsidiary, reincorporate in Delaware and change the company'sname. Reuter&#3;